verbose_text: Several transcription factors, such as peroxisome proliferator activated receptors, signal transducers and activators of transcription, CCAAT-enhancer-binding proteins, interferon regulatory factors, Kruppel like factors, GATA binding protein 3, nuclear transcription factor-kappaB, and c-MYC, were found to promote the expression of specific genes, which dictate the functional polarization of macrophages.
